984e5487-03a0-46de-8bdc-641caa24658d	Business Context Palmyra R&D needed a modern, scalable, and maintainable workflow engine capable of supporting complex business processes and future digitalization initiatives. The existing Activiti‑based engine showed limitations in performance, maintainability, and ecosystem support. This PoC was initiated to evaluate alternatives, validate technical feasibility, and define a future‑proof workflow architecture that could integrate multiple engines while ensuring backward compatibility and operational continuity. Role & Responsibilities - Conducted an in‑depth comparative PoC of Camunda, Flowable, Activiti, and jBPM, including benchmarks, stress tests, and licensing analysis. - Designed and implemented an adapter‑based architecture enabling workflow engines to remain pluggable and interchangeable with minimal downtime. - Performed backward compatibility studies between the legacy Activiti v6 engine and new candidates	{"loc": {"lines": {"to": 1, "from": 1}}, "source": "blob", "file_id": "1CqcqTB33HGhdzEJPS1_ErQKb8j6QcT6T", "blobType": "text/plain", "file_title": "workflow-engines-poc.txt"}	[0.005528586,0.029424328,0.08171376,-0.00698729,0.022720218,-0.00080302794,-0.017767869,0.02160067,0.052526508,-0.003477181,0.040171977,-0.043938924,-0.034350336,-0.0041093957,0.036563087,0.03248003,0.024037331,-0.04177886,-0.026842784,0.022930956,0.05473926,-0.01789958,-0.011142785,0.021811409,0.02252265,-0.038644128,-0.057478856,0.01627953,0.00016371316,-0.10863557,0.038301677,-0.04085688,-0.036668453,0.030636072,0.013296266,0.010773993,-0.0009211566,-0.0017221266,0.010102265,0.012137206,-0.021771895,-0.020046476,0.005732739,0.03682651,-0.0045111156,0.00094009016,0.0068555786,0.044202346,0.04767953,-0.021060653,-0.0029980808,-0.0036187707,0.04607265,-0.0033306521,-0.011880369,-0.021034312,0.022548992,0.004412332,-0.032295637,0.01732005,-0.008106837,-0.031215603,0.049470805,-0.014303858,-0.04067248,0.05281627,-0.051894292,0.013065771,0.0056273