08dec094-f8e0-40e1-bb65-2a91e4f5fdb4	Role & Responsibilities - Extended the Palmyra framework to support Apache Kafka and Amazon SQS based on client requirements and architectural constraints. - Integrated open‑source messaging features into Palmyra while ensuring full compatibility with existing domain models and data structures. - Designed a messaging abstraction layer to unify APIs and allow transparent switching between Kafka and SQS. - Implemented message validation, serialization, deserialization, and error‑handling mechanisms within the framework. - Collaborated with client teams to test, validate, and deploy messaging integrations in production environments. Technical Contributions - Built a unified messaging API enabling plug‑and‑play integration of Kafka and SQS without requiring code changes from client applications. - Implemented serialization and validation modules ensuring message integrity and schema consistency across distributed systems. - Integrated Kafka producers/consumers and SQS queue operations into	{"loc": {"lines": {"to": 1, "from": 1}}, "source": "blob", "file_id": "1g3SbHys3hE0ceOyg2K9cdYVjuPDgHoNN", "blobType": "text/plain", "file_title": "palmyra-messaging-ecosystem-enhancement.txt"}	[-0.0052578985,-0.0024263682,0.08127797,0.0037170548,0.024346557,-0.01065699,-0.048864998,-0.0074341097,0.01766752,-0.01944778,0.04017243,-0.050976753,-0.044985265,0.03528593,0.028189456,0.053726945,0.012805576,0.05156608,-0.026200479,0.036955692,0.022897795,0.034230053,-0.011129679,0.009159118,-0.027428243,-0.07111208,-0.06251773,0.062714174,-0.027256357,-0.08397905,0.03155353,-0.014131562,-0.052106295,0.010871848,0.013321238,-0.0019567485,-0.023143347,0.015322492,-0.031946413,0.029196223,-0.015838154,-0.06354906,-0.0036311115,0.01887073,-0.006857061,0.053874277,0.0018170904,0.03565426,0.002500034,0.008115519,0.0058134617,-0.015211994,0.07842955,-0.015973207,-0.0016743629,-0.015101495,0.011522563,0.034573827,-0.029810105,0.02573393,-0.04599203,-0.03631725,-