76	c750f1b8c87243caba61151b3318bc16	{"type": "ai", "content": "I’ve spent several years working with Java in the context of large‑scale, enterprise‑grade applications and frameworks. Below is a concise overview of the experience I’ve gathered from my recent projects:\\n\\n| Area | What I’ve Done |\\n|------|----------------|\\n| **Core Java** | Developed multithreaded, high‑throughput services; implemented concurrency and locking strategies to support heavy transactional workloads. |\\n| **Spring Ecosystem** | Built and maintained Spring‑based applications (Spring Core, Spring Data, Spring Boot). Handled transactional support, dependency injection, and configuration management. |\\n| **Persistence / ORM** | Worked extensively with **Hibernate**, **MyBatis**, and **Spring Data** for CRUD APIs, caching, and complex data‑mapping scenarios. Integrated with multiple RDBMSs (MSSQL, Oracle, PostgreSQL). |\\n| **Integration & Messaging** | Designed and extended integration pipelines using **Apache Camel** for data transformation (CSV, Excel, XML, JSON). Implemented messaging abstractions that bridge **RabbitMQ, ActiveMQ, Apache Kafka, and Amazon SQS**. |\\n| **Testing** | Wrote comprehensive unit‑test suites with **JUnit**, focusing on regression protection and framework stability. |\\n| **Deployment** | Packaged and deployed Java applications across a variety of servers (IBM WebSphere, JBoss, WildFly, Tomcat) and cloud environments, ensuring portability and consistent behavior. |\\n| **Framework Engineering** | Contributed to the **Palmyra** framework—a transversal, reusable library used by dozens of client applications. Enhanced core architecture, added cross‑cutting concerns (caching, transaction management, messaging), and ensured long‑term maintainability. |\\n| **Performance & Reliability** | Optimized persistence layers, refined caching strategies, and introduced robust error‑handling and validation for messaging pipelines, resulting in more reliable mission‑critical